00:38:50.330 --> 00:38:51.760
So when stocks are cheap--

00:38:51.760 --> 00:38:53.150
[LAUGHTER]

00:38:53.150 --> 00:38:56.060
--you really can buy
them at the right price.

00:38:56.060 --> 00:38:57.335
OK.

00:38:57.335 --> 00:39:00.560
And what I'd like to do
now is talk a little bit

00:39:00.560 --> 00:39:02.830
about the two areas
that I think are

00:39:02.830 --> 00:39:05.070
worth your while to look into.

00:39:05.070 --> 00:39:06.920
I don't see too
many opportunities

00:39:06.920 --> 00:39:08.770
in the stock market,
although there

00:39:08.770 --> 00:39:12.740
are individual sectors
and individual stocks that

00:39:12.740 --> 00:39:13.540
are reasonable.

00:39:13.540 --> 00:39:15.790
They're not dirt cheap,
but they're reasonable.

00:39:15.790 --> 00:39:18.160
But the areas that
are exciting me today

00:39:18.160 --> 00:39:20.580
are the energy markets
and the gold markets.

00:39:20.580 --> 00:39:23.730
And let's take energy first.

00:39:23.730 --> 00:39:28.790
As you know, in energy
we had $140 oil price.

00:39:28.790 --> 00:39:30.710
Everybody that
had a drilling rig

00:39:30.710 --> 00:39:32.430
when out and drilled for oil.

00:39:32.430 --> 00:39:35.230
We created this massive
surplus, and then the market

00:39:35.230 --> 00:39:36.190
turned down.

00:39:36.190 --> 00:39:38.530
And so we built
this huge surplus.

00:39:38.530 --> 00:39:43.250
And so the price went down
from $140 down to $26 to $28.

00:39:43.250 --> 00:39:45.614
Now if you read the
newspapers there,

00:39:45.614 --> 00:39:47.780
all you would have had to
do is read the newspapers,

00:39:47.780 --> 00:39:50.160
and you would have known that
you were in the value zone,

00:39:50.160 --> 00:39:52.560
because that's the
contrary opinion.

00:39:52.560 --> 00:39:54.610
All the experts were
saying that the oil

00:39:54.610 --> 00:39:57.430
was going to go down to $20,
maybe even in the teens.

00:39:57.430 --> 00:39:57.980
Who knows?

00:39:57.980 --> 00:39:59.036
Whatever.

00:39:59.036 --> 00:40:00.660
But the point about
it is if you looked

00:40:00.660 --> 00:40:03.275
at the fundamentals
today, the oil,

00:40:03.275 --> 00:40:05.590
the surplus is
kind of imbalanced.

00:40:05.590 --> 00:40:07.410
The way they
measured a surplus is

00:40:07.410 --> 00:40:09.900
by the number of
days of inventory.

00:40:09.900 --> 00:40:12.130
At the high point when
you have a lot of surplus,

00:40:12.130 --> 00:40:14.740
you can get 38
days of inventory.

00:40:14.740 --> 00:40:17.690
And at the low
point, it's 25 to 26.

00:40:17.690 --> 00:40:19.430
The average is about 32.

00:40:19.430 --> 00:40:22.710
So 32 days of average
inventory is when

00:40:22.710 --> 00:40:24.410
the market is in equilibrium.

00:40:24.410 --> 00:40:26.420
Then the rest is
supply and demand.

00:40:26.420 --> 00:40:28.110
OK.

00:40:28.110 --> 00:40:29.250
The average is 32.

00:40:29.250 --> 00:40:30.820
We are at 30.2.

00:40:30.820 --> 00:40:34.570
So we are getting into
equilibrium where it's even.

00:40:34.570 --> 00:40:37.510
It's even slightly
less than the average.

00:40:37.510 --> 00:40:39.030
So that's the positive.

00:40:39.030 --> 00:40:40.930
The other part is
that the production

00:40:40.930 --> 00:40:43.090
is going down dramatically.

00:40:43.090 --> 00:40:45.800
Throughout the world,
they have cut $1 trillion

00:40:45.800 --> 00:40:48.015
of capital expenditures.

00:40:48.015 --> 00:40:49.960
So you know, just
common sense says

00:40:49.960 --> 00:40:53.140
that the decline is coming in.

00:40:53.140 --> 00:40:55.470
So far, the demand,
surprisingly,

00:40:55.470 --> 00:40:58.610
which is surprising everybody,
demand keeps going up.

00:40:58.610 --> 00:41:01.930
And so the demand is going up,
the production is going down,

00:41:01.930 --> 00:41:03.780
the drilling rigs,
the percentage

00:41:03.780 --> 00:41:08.300
in drilling rigs in
operation are down 79%.

00:41:08.300 --> 00:41:11.050
So you know that
production is going down.

00:41:11.050 --> 00:41:15.100
And the projections are today
that the average inventory

00:41:15.100 --> 00:41:19.180
could go down to 26 days
by the end of the year,

00:41:19.180 --> 00:41:21.450
or let's call it nine months.

00:41:21.450 --> 00:41:23.790
And that would mean that
that would be the lowest

00:41:23.790 --> 00:41:26.272
inventory in 25 years.

00:41:26.272 --> 00:41:27.730
The other thing
you want to look at

00:41:27.730 --> 00:41:31.465
is that while you hear
about the productivity,

00:41:31.465 --> 00:41:33.450
that they've been
able to cut the costs,

00:41:33.450 --> 00:41:37.780
some people can produce oil
at $25 to $35 and so forth.

00:41:37.780 --> 00:41:43.060
However, if you want to produce
95 million barrels a day,

00:41:43.060 --> 00:41:44.960
which is what we
need, you're not

00:41:44.960 --> 00:41:47.150
going to do it on
$50 or $60 oil.

00:41:47.150 --> 00:41:51.550
The minimum that we
require is $60 to $65.

00:41:51.550 --> 00:41:53.320
That's the marginal cost of oil.

00:41:53.320 --> 00:41:55.180
In other words, most
companies are not

00:41:55.180 --> 00:41:58.810
going to go out and drill
unless they can make $65.

00:41:58.810 --> 00:42:01.260
Because some people
can do it, but there's

00:42:01.260 --> 00:42:04.550
not enough of that cheap oil
to be able to meet the demand.

00:42:04.550 --> 00:42:09.430
So we have to have a higher
price than $65 to $70.

00:42:09.430 --> 00:42:12.130
And with the way it's going
under production costs,

00:42:12.130 --> 00:42:15.330
I believe, it's my personal
opinion, by looking at this,

00:42:15.330 --> 00:42:18.110
talking to the companies,
talking to all these people

00:42:18.110 --> 00:42:21.470
who are very knowledgeable,
there is the possibility

00:42:21.470 --> 00:42:23.770
that if they don't start
the production soon,

00:42:23.770 --> 00:42:27.710
that one day we might even
have a temporary spike in oil.

00:42:27.710 --> 00:42:31.200
So the opportunities
in oil are there.

00:42:31.200 --> 00:42:33.260
The valuations are still good.

00:42:33.260 --> 00:42:36.370
And there's opportunities
in the stocks and the bonds,

00:42:36.370 --> 00:42:39.460
and that would be something I
would direct your attention in.

00:42:39.460 --> 00:42:43.310
The next thing I would like to
do is cover the gold market.

00:42:43.310 --> 00:42:46.500
Now let me say this.

00:42:46.500 --> 00:42:48.170
I am not a gold buyer.

00:42:48.170 --> 00:42:54.080
I have only owned gold
three times in 48 years.

00:42:54.080 --> 00:42:56.400
I am a value investor.

00:42:56.400 --> 00:43:01.440
And when a market goes down
for five straight years,

00:43:01.440 --> 00:43:05.780
and it goes down 85%, which is
what happened to this market,

00:43:05.780 --> 00:43:10.660
you are in market evaluations
that only happened 2% or 3%

00:43:10.660 --> 00:43:11.920
of the time.

00:43:11.920 --> 00:43:18.690
So buying into the gold
market at the turn of the year

00:43:18.690 --> 00:43:22.440
was like buying
into stocks in 1974.

00:43:22.440 --> 00:43:28.180
The market had gone down
five years, 85% down.

00:43:28.180 --> 00:43:31.027
Any time a market
goes down 65%, you

00:43:31.027 --> 00:43:32.610
want to dust it off
and start looking.

00:43:32.610 --> 00:43:36.800
But when you've got 85% decline,
that's pretty extraordinary.

00:43:36.800 --> 00:43:40.120
But here is a very
important statistic,

00:43:40.120 --> 00:43:44.270
and that is there
are $294 trillion

00:43:44.270 --> 00:43:47.362
worth of assets, cash stocks
and bonds, in the world.

00:43:47.362 --> 00:43:48.820
That's all the
assets in the world,

00:43:48.820 --> 00:43:52.006
not counting real estate.

00:43:52.006 --> 00:43:56.810
All the gold in the world
is only $7 trillion,

00:43:56.810 --> 00:44:00.270
and half of that is in
jewelry and technology.

00:44:00.270 --> 00:44:04.300
So you only have
about $3.5 trillion

00:44:04.300 --> 00:44:08.350
that is tradeable in gold,
and it's probably even less.

00:44:08.350 --> 00:44:13.830
Now if 1% of the people
into the $294 trillion

00:44:13.830 --> 00:44:17.070
decide to move 1% of
their assets into gold,

00:44:17.070 --> 00:44:19.800
that would be $2.9 trillion.

00:44:19.800 --> 00:44:23.950
That 1% would be enough to
absorb all the gold that's

00:44:23.950 --> 00:44:28.180
ever been mined in the world,
and that is extraordinary.

00:44:28.180 --> 00:44:31.190
And that is an
unusual opportunity.

00:44:31.190 --> 00:44:32.800
The market has come
up quite a bit,

00:44:32.800 --> 00:44:35.010
so I've cautioned diving in.

00:44:35.010 --> 00:44:36.340
It's worth looking into.

00:44:36.340 --> 00:44:39.980
Now let me just take a couple
of moments [INAUDIBLE].

00:44:39.980 --> 00:44:42.160
Well, what's going to
make people buy gold?

00:44:42.160 --> 00:44:44.300
It's been around
for 5,000 years.

00:44:44.300 --> 00:44:46.230
Why would they buy any more?

00:44:46.230 --> 00:44:48.240
Well, first of all,
there's $10 trillion

00:44:48.240 --> 00:44:51.440
in negative interest
rates today.

00:44:51.440 --> 00:44:53.820
We've never had that in
the history of the world,

00:44:53.820 --> 00:44:55.310
negative interest rates.

00:44:55.310 --> 00:44:57.420
So there's $10 trillion.

00:44:57.420 --> 00:44:59.000
There's $12 trillion
dollars that

00:44:59.000 --> 00:45:02.340
has been printed
throughout the world.

00:45:02.340 --> 00:45:04.620
That's another potential.

00:45:04.620 --> 00:45:07.660
We've got the enormous
worldwide debt.

00:45:07.660 --> 00:45:11.300
And more importantly, we've
got worldwide uncertainty.

00:45:11.300 --> 00:45:14.320
So I really believe that
over the next few years,

00:45:14.320 --> 00:45:17.380
there's going to be a tremendous
flow into these gold markets.

00:45:17.380 --> 00:45:19.770
And let me just say one
thing, which most people don't

00:45:19.770 --> 00:45:23.690
realize, and I hear everybody
who's critical of gold saying.

00:45:23.690 --> 00:45:28.740
Whenever we cut the ties
to gold in August of 1971--

00:45:28.740 --> 00:45:30.020
I'll never forget that day.

00:45:30.020 --> 00:45:32.830
I didn't think I could ever
believe that the United

00:45:32.830 --> 00:45:35.025
States would cut its link
with gold and the dollar,

00:45:35.025 --> 00:45:37.240
the dollar was always supreme.

00:45:37.240 --> 00:45:39.730
So we became a fiat currency.

00:45:39.730 --> 00:45:43.350
If you would have bought gold,
which we did at that time,

00:45:43.350 --> 00:45:48.140
the average return is
7.96% over 44 years.

00:45:48.140 --> 00:45:52.520
If you bought it 20 years ago,
the average return is 6.48%.

00:45:52.520 --> 00:45:54.040
And if you bought
it 10 years ago,

00:45:54.040 --> 00:45:56.560
the average return is about 8%.

00:45:56.560 --> 00:46:00.840
If you bought it at the top of
the market in 2011 till now,

00:46:00.840 --> 00:46:02.760
you would have lost 2.5%.

00:46:02.760 --> 00:46:06.580
The point I'm making, over
any 10 or 20-year period,

00:46:06.580 --> 00:46:09.750
you're going to make
6% to 9% on your money,

00:46:09.750 --> 00:46:12.170
irrespective of whether
it pays dividends.

00:46:12.170 --> 00:46:15.980
And I know you could do better,
but you could also do worse.

00:46:15.980 --> 00:46:19.610
In this type of environment, I
see it's a great opportunity.

00:46:19.610 --> 00:46:21.440
It's something you
should look into.

00:46:21.440 --> 00:46:24.510
Don't dive into it right away,
because it had a big run.

00:46:24.510 --> 00:46:26.440
But energy and
gold are something

00:46:26.440 --> 00:46:29.350
that are worthwhile
as a value investor

00:46:29.350 --> 00:46:31.930
that you want to look into.

00:46:31.930 --> 00:46:35.670
I want to summarize this
program with these things,

00:46:35.670 --> 00:46:38.770
to summarize the things that I
learned through my experience.

00:46:38.770 --> 00:46:41.440
First of all, always
seek the truth.

00:46:41.440 --> 00:46:44.340
Number two, develop your
own set of principles.

00:46:44.340 --> 00:46:45.980
Not the ones you
were taught, not

00:46:45.980 --> 00:46:48.210
the one part of your
religion, but the ones

00:46:48.210 --> 00:46:51.110
that you make and own
yourself, and the ones you're

00:46:51.110 --> 00:46:53.540
willing to make a sacrifice for.

00:46:53.540 --> 00:46:57.890
Be totally focused on everything
you do so you can not only

00:46:57.890 --> 00:47:01.170
harness your intelligence,
but the greater intelligence

00:47:01.170 --> 00:47:02.780
of your subconscious mind.

00:47:02.780 --> 00:47:06.710
It only comes through focusing.

00:47:06.710 --> 00:47:11.270
And by practicing the principle
and following the philosophy

00:47:11.270 --> 00:47:14.960
and sticking with it, you
develop tremendous faith

00:47:14.960 --> 00:47:16.340
and courage.

00:47:16.340 --> 00:47:18.700
And that's the kind
of thing you need

00:47:18.700 --> 00:47:21.350
to go through any difficult
time that you might

00:47:21.350 --> 00:47:24.080
have to go through your life.

00:47:24.080 --> 00:47:28.290
And finally, and the most
important one, never give up.

00:47:28.290 --> 00:47:29.276
Thank you very much.

